Ethiopia’s Edndale Belachew was crowned Two Oceans Marathon champion in Cape Town at the weekend after he crossed the finish line in 3:09:05. Nkosikhona Mhlakwana finished just three seconds behind Belachew, clocking 3:09:08. In the women’s race, South African Gerda Steyn walked away with the top prize after she finished the marathon in 3:29:42. Dubbed the “world’s most beautiful marathon”, the Two Oceans Marathon takes place over a distance of 56km from Main Road on the corner of Dean Street in Newlands to the University of Cape Town’s rugby fields on the upper campus of Rondebosch. For the latest sports news from Sunday World, click here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.